The paper proposes a new model for structured binary classification using Gaussian conditional random fields. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, specifically in the sub-field of structured prediction. The paper also discusses the computational and memory complexity of the proposed models, which suggests a focus on computer science and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of latent variables and the reduction of noise, which suggests a possible fit for the sub-categories cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
